# Application Settings

This file contains the environment variables required to run the application.

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Description | Default Value |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `DATABASE_URL` | The PostgreSQL connection string (using asyncpg). | `postgresql+asyncpg://cert_admin:your_strong_password@localhost:5432/cert_system` |
| `JWT_SECRET` | Secret key used for signing JWT tokens. | `change_me` |
| `JWT_ALGORITHM` | The algorithm used fgit rm -r --cached backend/.venvor JWT signing (e.g., HS256). | `HS256` |
| `JWT_EXPIRY_MINUTES` | Expiration time for admin/entity JWT tokens in minutes. | `60` |
| `CUSTOMER_JWT_EXPIRY_MINUTES` | Expiration time for customer JWT tokens in minutes. | `30` |
| `CORS_ORIGINS` | A comma-separated list of allowed origins for CORS. | `*` |
| `OTP_EXPIRY_SECONDS` | Expiration time for OTPs in seconds. | `300` |

## Example `.env` File Content

```env
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://cert_admin:your_strong_password@localhost:5432/cert_system
JWT_SECRET=super_secret_key_change_this_in_production
JWT_ALGORITHM=HS256
JWT_EXPIRY_MINUTES=60
CUSTOMER_JWT_EXPIRY_MINUTES=30
CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:5173,http://127.0.0.1:5173
OTP_EXPIRY_SECONDS=300
```
